Column Comment.0: BUSINESS ASSOCIATE: Unique identifier for the jurisdiction that is managing theland sale or bidding round.
Column Comment.1: LAND SALE NUMBER: A unique identifier for the land sale.
Column Comment.2: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y or N flag indicating whether this row of data is currentlyeither active/valid (Y) or inactive/invalid (N).
Column Comment.3: CLOSE DATE: The end date for postings to be submitted for the land sales
Column Comment.4: DESCRIPTION: General description of the land sale
Column Comment.5: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.6: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.7: LAND SALE NAME: name assigned to the land sale, bidding round, concessionoffering etc.
Column Comment.8: OPEN DATE: The start date for submissions to be submitted for posting requests ona particular land sale.
Column Comment.9: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.10: PUBLISH DATE: The date the land sale postings are published and made availableto the public
Column Comment.11: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.12: SALE DATE: The date the actual sale occurs.
Column Comment.13: SOLD SIZE: Total amount of land measured in hectares/acres in the parcel that wassold.
Column Comment.14: SOLD SIZE OUOM: Original units, Usually hectares or acres
Column Comment.15: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.16: TOTAL BONUS: The total cash payment by the lessee for the execution of a lease bythe mineral owner, expressed as dollars per hectare/acre.
Column Comment.17: TOTAL BONUS OUOM: Original units, Currency type
Column Comment.18: TOTAL SIZE: Total amount of land measured in hectares/acres in the parcelpublished on the land sale.
Column Comment.19: TOTAL SIZE OUOM: Original units, Usually hectares or acres
Column Comment.20: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.21: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.22: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.23: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.24: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.25: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.26: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
